title: Print, "Membership Certificate, Society of Journeymen Cabinet-Makers", August 2, 1796
medium: Engraving, pen and brown ink, sealing wax on paper
description: An escutcheon relating to cabinet-making in center, flanked by desk and chair. Below, legend with the recipient, John Hewitt; Secretary W. Philip; Chairman Edward Barkhouse and date written with pen and brown ink. Red wax seal on bottom.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Membership Certificate, Society of Journeymen Cabinet-Makers", August 2, 1796.
August 2, 1796. Engraving, pen and brown ink, sealing wax on paper. Gift of Cooper Union Library. 1953-10-80.
